t 3.2x10^26 erg and matches the radiative losses. It could be supplied\nby magnetic flux loss of the sunspot (7.5x10^27 erg), kinetic energy from the\nincrease in the LB width (4x10^28 erg), or freefall of mass along the coronal\nloops (6.3x10^26 ,erg).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Jan 2023 11:47:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
